				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, recently I had a bard friend of mine hold onto my singing steel helm so I could help camp her one of her own.(They're lore).  Unfortunately the next day her comp fried out and I guess she won't be back on EQ for a few months according to the e-mail I got.  So....now it becomes priority for me to re-obtain an SS helm.
<br />

<br />
But I'm begining to question whether that's reasonable anymore.
<br />

<br />
Of the last 3 &quot;Froggy's&quot; I've killed, 1 dropped some crappy Beastlord helm, and 2....were tottally empty.
<br />

<br />
I thought at first this was a fluke...since when do sebilis named drop &quot;Nothing&quot; as part of their loot table?  Then I killed a few other named in the area, such as Armorer and Chef, and I found them to be empty too.
<br />

<br />
Now, I never really did this camp in ages, but I coulda swore the last time I never got any empty named in Sebilis, ever.  This change really blows if it is a true nerf, because honestly Sebilis sees right about zero traffic these days and this is even more incentive to turn it into another &quot;Dead&quot; zone.</span></td>
