			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Sebilis named Nerfed or has it always been this way?<a name="49722"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 2 04 11:12 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'll go with &quot;always been this way&quot;... but it hasn't ALWAYS been that way.  I'll explain.
<br />

<br />
When Sebilis was originally itemized, 2 of the Singing Steel armor pieces were forgotten.  (Singing Steel Helm and... Bracer?)
<br />

<br />
We determined that nearly all other classes had helms, vambraces, and braces dropping in Sebilis.  Since the helm and bracer weren't dropping in Karnor's either, we presumed the bard ones were supposed to as well.
<br />

<br />
Verant fixed their oversight by making new mobs specifically to drop them, placing those mobs in unused rooms of Sebilis.  Rather than having a common, uncommon, and rare drop like everything else, the ONLY drop on these mobs was the singing steel piece at uncommon.  (It was a quick fix.)  It is good that they were there now, but the lack of sebilite scale and rare drops made it hard to get groups to camp there.  On the good side, it was easier to find this camp open than others in Seb.
<br />

<br />
More loot has since been added to these, but this didn't completely fill the &quot;holes&quot; in the loot table.
<br />

<br />
- Lall
<br />
Bold Bardess with 113 Melodic Tools
<br />
Shards of Avalon, Xegony.</span></td>
