				<td colspan="2"><span>On the bright side, if you have a group that is getting good XP in Sebilis -- and any group within a couple levels of 58 should get pretty good XP there -- then the two camps in question are really good for constant, steady pulls, a variety of sellable loot, and a shot at your singing steel drops.  Of the two, Chef and Disco, I think Chef is easier to keep clear and is a bit safer to handle, but the Disco camp might have better loot, overall, with access to the Tolan's Darkwood Bracer - always a VERY good seller.  But I found hours spent duoing these camps at level 62 to still be fairly decent AA xp and very good money.</span></td>
